Package org.openwms.core.exception

This package contains common used exception types.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ExceptionCodes
    A ExceptionCodes.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DataException Deprecated
    Use IntegrationRuntimeException instead
    DataNotFoundException
    A DataNotFoundException is thrown to indicate that data was expected but not found.
    DomainModelException
    A DomainModelException is a checked top-level exception for all exceptions of the domain model layer.
    DomainModelRuntimeException
    A DomainModelRuntimeException is an unchecked top-level exception for all unhandled runtime exceptions of the domain model layer.
    IllegalConfigurationValueException
    An IllegalConfigurationValueException is thrown to signal an invalid or unexpected configured value, usually derived from a configuration file that is maintained by developers or users.
    IntegrationRuntimeException Deprecated
    Use IntegrationLayerException instead
    InvalidPasswordException
    An InvalidPasswordException indicates that a password is not confirm with the defined rules.
    NoUniqueResultException
    A NoUniqueResultException is thrown when a single result was expected but multiple entities were found.
    ResourceNotFoundException
    A ResourceNotFoundException is thrown when a given resource couldn't be resolved.
    WrongClassTypeException
    A WrongClassTypeException.

Package org.openwms.core.exception Description
